
    Merkel's choice elected ruling party leader

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 EPA
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Ms Kramp-Karrenbauer was seen as Ms Merkel's heir apparent
                
            Germany's ruling Christian Democrat Union has chosen Annegret Kramp-Karrenbauer as the new party leader, but Angela Merkel plans to serve out her term as chancellor.The former chief minister of Saarland won 517 of the 999 votes cast.She narrowly defeated Friedrich Merz, a millionaire lawyer, who received 482 votes at the party conference.As the head of Germany's largest party, Ms Kramp-Karrenbauer could become the next German chancellor.This breaking news story is being updated and more details will be published shortly. Please refresh the page for the fullest version.
    
        
